Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Bring a large #saucepan{} 
of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} to the boil for the potatoes.

Meanwhile, trim the @carrot{1}(trimmed and quartered lengthways), then quarter 
lengthways (no need to peel). Slice widthways into pieces about 1/2cm thick.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{3}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Peel and 
slice the @potatoes{450%g} into 1cm thick rounds. Once boiling, add the potato 
slices to the water and simmer until just tender, ~{8-12%mins}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. 
Once hot, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g}, @British beef mince{240%g} 
and carrot to the pan and fry until browned, ~{5-6%mins}. Use a spoon to break 
the mince up as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's cooked 
> when no longer pink in the middle. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Once browned, add half the garlic to the meat and cook for ~{1%min}. Stir in 
the @tomato passata{1%carton}, @red wine stock paste{28%g} and @sugar{1/2%tsp}. 
Lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{4-5%mins}.

Once the potatoes are cooked, carefully drain in a #colander{}. Wipe out the 
(now empty) saucepan and return to medium heat with a drizzle of oil. Once hot, 
add the remaining garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{30%secs}. Stir in the 
@creme fraiche{150%g}, @chicken stock paste{10%g} and @water{50%ml}. Mix 
together, bring to the boil, then remove from the heat. Season to taste with 
salt and pepper.

Once the beef and bacon mixture is ready, spoon into an appropriately sized 
#ovenproof dish{}.

Carefully lay the cooked potato slices in layers over the top, then pour over 
the creamy sauce. Sprinkle over the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g}.

Bake on the top shelf of your oven until golden brown and bubbly, 
~{15-20%mins}.

> TIP: Put the dish onto a #baking tray{} to catch any drips.

Once ready, share the dauphinoise cottage pie out between your plates and tuck 
in. Enjoy!